tool_description: Search events and venues on Eventful's local event database.
name: Eventful
title: Eventful

api_list.name: searchEvents
api_list.description: Search for events.

optional_parameters.name: date
optional_parameters.description: Limit this list of results to a date range, specified by label or exact range. Currently supported labels include: `All`, `Future`, `Past`, `Today`, `Last Week`, `This Week`, `Next week`, and months by name, e.g. `October`. Exact ranges can be specified the form 'YYYYMMDD00-YYYYMMDD00', for example '2012042500-2012042700'; the last two digits of each date in this format are ignored.

optional_parameters.name: imageSizes
optional_parameters.description: A comma separted list of image_sizes desired.

optional_parameters.name: exCategory
optional_parameters.description: Exclude search results from including this category ID.

optional_parameters.name: sortOrder
optional_parameters.description: One of 'popularity', 'date', or 'relevance'. Default is 'relevance'.

optional_parameters.name: keywords
optional_parameters.description: The search keywords.

optional_parameters.name: changeMultiDayStart
optional_parameters.description: If set changes the start_date of long duration events (lasting multiple days) to the beginning of the search date range. It will also give the next occurence of a recurring event after the start range.

optional_parameters.name: oauthToken
optional_parameters.description: OAuth Access Token from `getAccessToken` method.

optional_parameters.name: pageSize
optional_parameters.description: The desired number of results per page.

optional_parameters.name: units
optional_parameters.description: One of "mi" or "km", the units of the "within" parameter. Defaults to "mi".

optional_parameters.name: mature
optional_parameters.description: Sets the level of filtering for events marked as "mature" due to keywords in the title or description. One of 'all' (no filtering), 'normal', or 'safe'.

optional_parameters.name: category
optional_parameters.description: Limit the search results to this category ID. A list of categories may be specified separated by commas. See /categories/list for a list of categories and their IDs.

optional_parameters.name: countOnly
optional_parameters.description: If count_only is set, an abbreviated version of the output will be returned. Only total_items and search_time elements are included in the result.

optional_parameters.name: within
optional_parameters.description: If within is set and the "location" parameter resolves to a specific geolocation, the search will be restricted to the specified radius. If the "location" parameter does not resolve to a specific location, this parameter is ignored.

optional_parameters.name: sortDirection
optional_parameters.description: One of 'ascending' or 'descending'. Default varies by sort_order.

optional_parameters.name: location
optional_parameters.description: A location name to use in filtering the search results. Locations in the form `San Diego`, `San Diego, TX`, `London, United Kingdom`, and `Calgary, Alberta, Canada` are accepted, as are postal codes (`92122`) and venue IDs (`V0-001-000268633-5`). Common geocoordinate formats (`32.746682, -117.162741`) are also accepted, but the `within` parameter is required in order to set a search radius

optional_parameters.name: oauthTokenSecret
optional_parameters.description: OAuth Access Token Secret from `getAccessToken` method.

optional_parameters.name: languages
optional_parameters.description: Return our guess of each event language. ("Undetermined" is a possibility)

optional_parameters.name: pageNumber
optional_parameters.description: The desired page number

optional_parameters.name: include
optional_parameters.description: Indicates that optional sections should be included in the result XML.

api_list.name: createEvent
api_list.description: Add a new event record.

required_parameters.name: venueId
required_parameters.description: The ID of the venue where this event occurs.

required_parameters.name: oauthTokenSecret
required_parameters.description: OAuth Access Token Secret from `getAccessToken` method.

required_parameters.name: startTime
required_parameters.description: The event start time in ISO 8601 format (e.g. '2005-03-01T19:00:00') or a readable alternative (e.g. '2005-03-01 19:00:00').

optional_parameters.name: free
optional_parameters.description: True ("1") if the event is free, false ("0") otherwise.

optional_parameters.name: stopTime
optional_parameters.description: The event stop time, if any, in ISO 8601 format (see above).

optional_parameters.name: privacy
optional_parameters.description: The privacy setting for this event. (1 = public, 2 = private, 3 = semi-private) (optional, defaults to 1)

optional_parameters.name: allDay
optional_parameters.description: True ("1") if the event is an all-day event, false ("0") otherwise. (optional)

optional_parameters.name: tzOlsonPath
optional_parameters.description: The event timezone, as listed in the Olson timezones database (e.g. "America/New_York")

optional_parameters.name: price
optional_parameters.description: A text string describing the event price. For example, this could indicate a price range ("$15 - $35"), free but donations requested ("$10 donation suggested"), or other special instructions ("Adults $15, children under eight $5"). Don't pass this parameter or leave it blank if there is no price information

optional_parameters.name: parentId
optional_parameters.description: The ID of this event's parent event.

optional_parameters.name: tags
optional_parameters.description: A space-delimited list of tags.

optional_parameters.name: description
optional_parameters.description: The event description.

api_list.name: searchVenues

optional_parameters.description: One of 'popularity', 'relevance', or 'venue_name'. Default is 'relevance'.

optional_parameters.name: pageSize
optional_parameters.description: The desired number of results per page.

optional_parameters.name: oauthTokenSecret
optional_parameters.description: OAuth Access Token Secret from `getAccessToken` method.

optional_parameters.name: location
optional_parameters.description: A location name to use in filtering the search results. Locations in the form "San Diego", "San Diego, TX", "London, United Kingdom", and "Calgary, Alberta, Canada" are accepted.

optional_parameters.name: within
optional_parameters.description: If within is set and the location parameter resolves to a specific geolocation, the search will be restricted to the specified radius.

optional_parameters.name: units
optional_parameters.description: One of "mi" or "km", the units of the "within" parameter. Defaults to "mi".

optional_parameters.description: OAuth Access Token from `getAccessToken` method.

optional_parameters.name: pageNumber
optional_parameters.description: The desired page number.

optional_parameters.name: countOnly
optional_parameters.description: If count_only is set, an abbreviated version of the output will be returned. Only total_items and search_time elements are included in the result.

optional_parameters.name: sortDirection
optional_parameters.description: One of 'ascending' or 'descending'. Default varies by sort_order.

api_list.name: updateSingleEvent
api_list.description: Modify an event record.

required_parameters.name: oauthTokenSecret
required_parameters.description: OAuth Access Token Secret from `getAccessToken` method.

optional_parameters.name: price
optional_parameters.description: A text string describing the event price. For example, this could indicate a price range ("$15 - $35"), free but donations requested ("$10 donation suggested"), or other special instructions ("Adults $15, children under eight $5"). Don't pass this parameter or leave it blank if there is no price information

optional_parameters.name: parentId
optional_parameters.description: The ID of this event's parent event.

optional_parameters.name: description
optional_parameters.description: The event description.

optional_parameters.name: startTime
optional_parameters.description: The event start time in ISO 8601 format (e.g. '2005-03-01T19:00:00') or a readable alternative (e.g. '2005-03-01 19:00:00').

optional_parameters.name: tags
optional_parameters.description: A space-delimited list of tags.

optional_parameters.name: tzOlsonPath
optional_parameters.description: The event timezone, as listed in the Olson timezones database (e.g. "America/New_York")

optional_parameters.name: allDay
optional_parameters.description: True ("1") if the event is an all-day event, false ("0") otherwise. (optional)

optional_parameters.name: stopTime
optional_parameters.description: The event stop time, if any, in ISO 8601 format (see above).

optional_parameters.name: title
optional_parameters.description: The event title.

optional_parameters.name: privacy
optional_parameters.description: The privacy setting for this event. (1 = public, 2 = private, 3 = semi-private) (optional, defaults to 1)

optional_parameters.name: venueId
optional_parameters.description: The ID of the venue where this event occurs.

optional_parameters.name: free
optional_parameters.description: True ("1") if the event is free, false ("0") otherwise.
